text: Mendbayryn Naratsetseg also written as Mendbayryn Narantsetseg is a former Mongolian long track speed skater, who was active in the 1960s. Naratsetseg was, together with Tsedenjavyn Lhamjav, the fist Mongolian women to represent their nation at the World Championships. She participated at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1961, finishing 30th overall, and also at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1962, also finishing 30th overall. == Records== === Personal records === ==References== Category:Place of birth missing (living people) Category:Date of birth missing (living people) Category:Mongolian female speed skaters Category:Living people
